The guide of NEB calculation

*****Usage************************************************************************
Firstly, you shold know the optimized initial and final structure.
If you know the energies and forces of these structures too,
you can skip the calculation of both structures.

There are two ways to give structures.

* Only initial and final structure
=> intermediate structures are automatically generated with linear interpolation

* Start from desireble structure
=> Please write systemlabel.NEB and start calculation with UseSaveNEB=.true.
=> Please prepare syatemlabel.NEB just like an example.
=> Units are eV and Angstrom.
=> If you do not know some values (e.g. forces of intermediate structure or energies),
=> just substitute 0.0

Parallelization is available.
You can choose arbital number of beads.

**** INPUT OPTIONS****************************************************************
# MD options
MD.TypeOfRun            neb         # Type of dynamics = neb
MD.NumNEBsteps          30          # Maximum Number of NEB steps
MD.NumOfImages          4           # Number of Images ( intermediate structure )
MD.Kspring              0.02        # Spring force; default works well
MD.IndexOfNEB           5           # n>0 => CI-NEB from nth step
                                    # n>NumNEBsteps => IT-NEB
                                    # n=-1 => bisection-NEB
NEB.UseBroyden          .true.      # .true.  Broyden optimizer
                                    # .false. projected Verlet
MD.LengthTimeStep        0.3  fs    # time step for projected Verlet
NEB.SkipEdge            .false.     # Skip calculations of initial and 
                                    #  final states ; UseSaveNEB must be .ture.
MD.MaxCGDispl           0.04 Ang    # Maximum atomic displacement
MD.MaxForceTol          0.06 eV/Ang # Tolerance of force for each images
MD.UseSaveNEB           .false.     # You can start from arbitary continuations

NEB.ReferEtot           .false.     # .true. for the SIESTA
                                    # .false. under the finite bias
NEB.InterpolationScheme  spline     # linear, polynomial or spline
NEB.derivative1          0.0        # In the case of spline, boundary consitions should be suplied
NEB.derivativeN          0.0        # If the endpoints are stable states, 0.0

#Structure
%block FinalAtomicCoordinatesAndSpecies # if you do not start from .NEB file, put the coordinates of final state
                                        # in the same order of your %block AtomicCoordinatesAndSpecies

**** OUTPUTS *****************************************************************

* systemlabel.NEB *
The most recent reaction coordinates and gradients are written.
This can be used for the restarting.
It Contains energy (eV) , positon (Ang) , and TRUE forces for each bead

* systemlabel.neb_history *
The history of the coordinates, gradients and NEB forces of all intermadiate images.

**** Utility *********************************************************************

* neb2xsf
 Creates .AXSF file from .NEB file

* neb2ener
 Calculates PES form ~.NEB file, by integrating forces.
 Please input the file nema , "~.NEB", the number of bead and the number of atoms
>Outputs
 "landscape" ... potential energy surface
 "potential" ... above values corresponding to beads positions
